    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>How to: Translate an Element</Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow/>
      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph>This example shows how to translate, or move, an element with a transform. To translate an element, use a TranslateTransform. Use the transform's X property to specify the amount, in pixels, to move the element along the x-axis. Use the Y property to specify the amount, in pixels, to move the element along the y-axis. Finally, apply the TranslateTransform to the element's RenderTransform property. 
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>In the following example, a TranslateTransform is used to move an element 50 pixels to the right and 50 pixels down.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22">Example
    </Paragraph>

    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>XAML </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph xml:space="preserve" TextAlignment="Left" FontSize="8pt" FontFamily="Courier New"><Run>
&lt;Rectangle Height="50" Width="50" Fill="#CCCCCCFF" Stroke="Blue" StrokeThickness="2" Canvas.Left="100" Canvas.Top="100"> 
&lt;Rectangle.RenderTransform> 
&lt;TranslateTransform X="50" Y="50" /> 
&lt;/Rectangle.RenderTransform> 
&lt;/Rectangle> </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph>The TranslateTransform class is particularly useful for moving elements inside panels that don't support absolute positioning. For example, by applying a TranslateTransform to an element's RenderTransform property, you can move an element within a StackPanel or DockPanel.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>This example is part of a larger sample; 
for the complete sample, see the 2-D Transforms Sample.
    </Paragraph>

